-- Tharisa Minerals Gets 1 Billion Rand Bank Funding, Nedbank Says
-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 2012-03-06T14:52:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/tharisa-minerals-gets-1-billion-rand-bank-funding-nedbank-says.html
Tharisa Minerals (Pty) Ltd. got 1
billion rand ($131 million) from  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) ,  Nedbank
Group Ltd. (NED)  and  Absa Group Ltd. (ASA)  for a 4.8 million metric ton
chrome and platinum mine and concentrator plant in South Africa.  “All three banks were appointed jointly as the mandated
lead arrangers to Tharisa,” Nedbank said today in an e-mailed
statement. “All three banks are lenders to Tharisa, with HSBC
appointed as facility agent and account bank.” They provided
about 333.3 million rand of funding each, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
 jmarais@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
